&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dynamite Games is at the forefront of creating unparalleled gaming experiences for digital natives and the next generation of gamers. Our commitment to innovation and quality drives us to develop games that are not only visually stunning but also deeply engaging. Leveraging cutting-edge technology, we strive to deliver experiences that resonate with modern gamers, offering unique narratives and immersive gameplay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Software Engineer to join our team and contribute to the development of web-based and game-related applications. You will work with modern technologies to create seamless gaming experiences, from backend infrastructure to interactive front-end features. This is an opportunity to work in an exciting, fast-paced environment where you can take ownership of projects and see your work impact the gaming world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Develop and maintain gaming-related web applications using modern frameworks like Ruby on Rails, C# .NET&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Write and optimize code in JavaScript and Python to support game-related services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Utilize Git for version control and collaborate with other developers to create high-quality products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manage dependencies and libraries using NPM, PIP, and Ruby Gems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work with SQL and NoSQL databases (MongoDB, MySQL, MSSQL) to store and manage game data efficiently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Develop and maintain ReactJS applications for game UI components and player engagement platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collaborate with game designers, developers, and product managers to create interactive and engaging gaming solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Think Will Be A Great Fit:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum 3 years of relevant experience with Ruby on Rails is a must&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience with at least one of these web development frameworks (Ruby on Rails, C# .NET).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proficiency in JavaScript and Python for game-related scripting and web application development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong understanding of Git and version control workflows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Familiarity with package management tools like NPM, PIP, and Ruby Gems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge of SQL and NoSQL databases is a plus (MongoDB, MySQL, MSSQL).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience with ReactJS or other JavaScript frameworks is a bonus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Background in game development or experience building gaming-related applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You have passion in game development and are eager to learn.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are ambitious and wanna be a part of a growing startup.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You take ownership of your work and you take pride in the products you build.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You don&#39;t care about big company politics, you care about building high quality products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are interested in games and want to know what&#39;s powering this billion dollar industry&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dynamite Games is at the forefront of creating unparalleled gaming experiences for digital natives and the next generation of gamers. Our commitment to innovation and quality drives us to develop games that are not only visually stunning but also deeply engaging. Leveraging cutting-edge technology, we strive to deliver experiences that resonate with modern gamers, offering unique narratives and immersive gameplay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated and creative Game Designer to join our dynamic team here at Dynamite Games. As a Game Designer, you will collaborate closely with our design, audio, and development teams to assist in the creation and refinement of our games. This role requires a keen eye for detail, a passion for gaming, and excellent documentation skills to ensure ideas are clearly communicated and implemented effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the preparation and development of comprehensive Game Design Documents (GDDs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and analyse fair, balanced mathematical models, systems, and content that align with the game&#39;s overall creative direction to meet requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write and refine game rules and mechanics to ensure clarity and user engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure high standards of documentation are maintained throughout the design process, ensuring clear and concise communication across teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work alongside other game designers and developers to problem-solve and create exciting and innovative games concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct playtests, gather feedback, and suggest design improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor competitor products, industry trends and emerging game mechanics to contribute informed perspectives during discussions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply a data-driven design mindset for systems/content design through careful analysis of user feedback and key metrics to adjust gameplay and balance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate effectively with other departments of the development team (Tech, Art, QA, Product, etc) to ensure design alignment and deliver the best product possible.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Think Will Be A Great Fit:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ year(s) of experience in game design or related field (internships and personal projects considered).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Game Design, Computer Science, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good understanding of game mechanics and mathematical models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent documentation skills with attention to detail in creating clear and structured documents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with design tools (e.g. Figma, or similar software) and version control systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of game audio design and its role in player engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong collaboration and communication skills to work effectively in a team-oriented environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for gaming and a strong desire to grow within the industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with game engines such as Cocos Creator and Unity;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with agile production methodologies and relevant project management tools such as JIRA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills in both English and Chinese Mandarin to work with Chinese stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creative flair with an ability to think outside the box and push design boundaries.&lt;/li&

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dynamite Games is at the forefront of creating unparalleled gaming experiences for digital natives and the next generation of gamers. Our commitment to innovation and quality drives us to develop games that are not only visually stunning but also deeply engaging. Leveraging cutting-edge technology, we strive to deliver experiences that resonate with modern gamers through unique narratives and immersive gameplay — while also delivering B2B iGaming solutions to partners across the gaming industry. Part of the Rarespawn Ventures group, we operate across Singapore, Malaysia, Philippines, Taiwan and Vietnam, with a growing presence in key markets globally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated and creative Game Designer to join our dynamic team here at Dynamite Games. As a Game Designer, you will collaborate closely with our design, audio, and development teams to assist in the creation and refinement of our games. This role requires a keen eye for detail, a passion for gaming, and excellent documentation skills to ensure ideas are clearly communicated and implemented effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the preparation and development of comprehensive Game Design Documents (GDDs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write and refine game rules and mechanics to ensure clarity and user engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the Game Audio Designer to synchronize sound elements with game design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work alongside senior designers and developers to create exciting and innovative slot game concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct playtests, gather feedback, and suggest design improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure high standards of documentation are maintained throughout the design process, ensuring clear and concise communication across teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay updated on industry trends and emerging design practices to contribute fresh ideas to the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Think Will Be A Great Fit:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ year(s) of experience in game design or related field (internships and personal projects considered).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good understanding of game mechanics and game math knowledge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent documentation skills with attention to detail in creating clear and structured documents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with design tools (e.g., Adobe XD, Figma, or similar software) and version control systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of game audio design and its role in player engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong collaboration and communication skills to work effectively in a team-oriented environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for gaming and a strong desire to grow within the industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are:&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;Rarespawn Ventures is a Singapore-headquartered entertainment group and global venture builder operating across gaming, esports, and media. We build and scale ventures that harness technology, original content and strategic media solutions to deliver unparalleled experiences to gaming and esports communities worldwide. With offices across Southeast Asia and partners in key markets globally, we bring together passionate teams united by a love for gaming and a drive to build for the long term.&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;We operate in a fast moving and internationally regulated industry. We are actively searching for a qualified &lt;strong&gt;Legal Counsel &lt;/strong&gt;to build and lead the legal function across the group. The role is based in Singapore / Kuala Lumpur and reports directly to the Chief Executive Officer. The individual will also collaborate with other heads of department and will be expected to engage with key stakeholders such as the business team.&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;This is a hands-on role for a dynamic individual comfortable working across corporate, regulatory, commercial, and intellectual property matters in a multi-entity, multi-jurisdictional structure. The ideal candidate will not only ensure legal conformity but also work proactively to minimize the exposure of any legal risk while being commercially minded.&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regulatory &amp;amp; Licensing&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Lead all regulatory matters, including licensing applications, renewals, and ongoing compliance across relevant jurisdictions.&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Monitor evolving regulations across target markets and advise the business on market entry, restrictions, and compliance obligations.&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Liaise with external advisers on all regulatory matters and ongoing compliance.&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Corporate &amp;amp; Structuring&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Advise on and maintain the group&#39;s corporate structure.&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Manage corporate governance across the group entities.&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Support any M&amp;amp;A and corporate restructuring as the group grows.&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commercial Contracts&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Draft, review, and negotiate B2B licensing and marketing agreements.&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&q

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dynamite Games is at the forefront of creating unparalleled gaming experiences for digital natives and the next generation of gamers. Our commitment to innovation and quality drives us to develop games that are not only visually stunning but also deeply engaging. Leveraging cutting-edge technology, we strive to deliver experiences that resonate with modern gamers, offering unique narratives and immersive gameplay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an Operations Support Associate to join our ranks of growing game lovers, to support our growing operational needs. You will be working with a team of very experienced producer, game developers, artists and designer to create and operationalize HTML5 games.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a vibrant and fun work environment, there are plenty of gaming sessions and sharing sessions both internally (within the studios) and externally. If you enjoy building small to midsize game projects, if you think that you have what it takes to develop a successful product line of mobile games, we encourage you to apply now and find out more about what we have to offer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Assist to answer customer support requests via our Jira ticketing system&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Follow a planned schedule to monitor and manage live games configuration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Assist with product smoke testing and pre-production Testing tasks&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Taking ownership of customer issues reported and seeing problems through to resolution&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Provide prompt and accurate feedback to customers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Assist the QA (Quality Assurance) Team to verify and report bug&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Liaise with the Development Team to ensure game releases run smoothly&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Conduct risk assessment for games in development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Plan and design fraud tools for high-risk games&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Processes and workflows enhancement as assigned, including documentation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Rotate 8-hour night shifts or other shifts, as and when required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Occasional on-call escalation duties may be required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Think Will Be A Great Fit:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● A Diploma or Degree in Software/Computer Science/Computing/Computer Engineering/IT discipline or equivalent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● You have worked at least 1-3 years in an operations or technology support role&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Willingness to learn and stay informed about evolving industry trends and game standards&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● You are an avid gamer and passionate about learning more about the industry&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Driven and self-motivated, proactive and work well within a team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Excellent problem-solving and communication skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(The candidate should be comfortable working on night and other rotating shifts, as and when required)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dynamite Games is at the forefront of creating unparalleled gaming experiences for digital natives and the next generation of gamers. Our commitment to innovation and quality drives us to develop games that are not only visually stunning but also deeply engaging. Leveraging cutting-edge technology, we strive to deliver experiences that resonate with modern gamers, offering unique narratives and immersive gameplay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are seeking a dynamic and detail-oriented Projects Manager to oversee the development and execution of our games.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ideal candidate will be responsible for managing cross-functional teams, ensuring timely project delivery, and maintaining the highest standards of quality and innovation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will play a key role in bridging creative, technical, and business aspects to produce successful gaming experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the full lifecycle of our games, from concept to release and post-launch support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with game designers, developers, artists, and other stakeholders to ensure seamless production processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain project schedules, timelines, and milestones, ensuring projects are delivered on time and within budget.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and mitigate risks, identifying potential roadblocks and implementing solutions to keep projects on track.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a deep understanding of market trends, competitor products, and player preferences to make informed development decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with marketing, sales, and operations teams to align production with business objectives and go-to-market strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct quality assurance checks and player feedback analysis to drive continuous improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Think Will Be A Great Fit:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience in game production or a similar role, with a proven track record of delivering shipped games.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of game development pipelines and production methodologies (Agile, Scrum, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent project management skills with experience using tools like Jira, Trello, or Asana.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to balance project demands with creative essentials. You demand quality; creativity and fun while managing project resources and timelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong leadership, communication, and problem-solving skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with RNG mechanics and game mathematics is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dynamite Games is at the forefront of creating unparalleled gaming experiences for digital natives and the next generation of gamers. Our commitment to innovation and quality drives us to develop games that are not only visually stunning but also deeply engaging. Leveraging cutting-edge technology, we strive to deliver experiences that resonate with modern gamers through unique narratives and immersive gameplay — while also delivering B2B iGaming solutions to partners across the gaming industry. Part of the Rarespawn Ventures group, we operate across Singapore, Malaysia, Philippines, Taiwan and Vietnam, with a growing presence in key markets globally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of the Quality Assurance (QA) team, you will play an integral role in the testing process to ensure the quality and performance of our top-rated mobile applications. Following established requirements and checklists, you will be responsible for identifying, documenting, and reporting bugs in the designated bug tracking systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will collaborate closely with producers and programmers throughout the entire application development lifecycle, working alongside teams based in Singapore, Kuala Lumpur, and Ho Chi Minh City. This role offers the opportunity to gain comprehensive insights into the development and optimization of applications across a wide range of mobile devices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with developers and designers to test, debug, and optimize mobile applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review requirements, specifications, and technical design documents to provide clear, actionable feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Estimate, prioritize, plan, and coordinate testing activities to meet project deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop detailed, comprehensive, and well-structured test plans and test cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, document, and thoroughly track bugs, ensuring timely resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize bug tracking tools to report and manage issues throughout the development lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, develop, and maintain automation scripts to enhance testing efficiency, accuracy, and coverage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Think Will Be A Great Fit:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 4 years of experience in Quality Assurance (QA).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong command of English, with proficiency in speaking, reading, and writing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with QA platforms, tools, and related software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in automation programming languages such as Python, Selenium, or similar technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly self-motivated with a strong desire to learn and continuously acquire new knowledge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional attention to detail and commitment to delivering high-quality work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;Who We Are&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rarespawn Ventures is a Singapore-headquartered entertainment group and global venture builder operating across gaming, esports, iGaming, and media. We build and scale ventures that harness technology, original content and strategic media to deliver unparalleled experiences to gaming, esports, and entertainment communities worldwide. With offices across Southeast Asia and partners in key markets globally, we bring together passionate teams united by a love for gaming and a drive to build for the long term.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;The Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced and credible Regional Head of HR to lead the people function across our multi-country operations comprising approximately 180 staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting directly to the CEO, this is the most senior HR role in the organisation. You will own the full HR agenda — from governance and compliance to talent, culture, and capability building — across Singapore, Malaysia, Philippines, Taiwan and Vietnam. You will lead a lean regional HR team and work directly with in-country operators and business leaders to ensure the HR function is operationally excellent, commercially aware and genuinely trusted by the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on leadership role in an HR function that is amidst transformation. The expectation is that you will be as comfortable rolling up your sleeves on operational matters as you are advising the CEO on people strategy. This role will suit you if you thrive in ambiguous environments where you can shape something meaningful from the ground up.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;HR Strategy &amp;amp; Business Partnership&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary HR advisor to the CEO and senior leadership on all people matters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute a regional HR strategy aligned to business priorities; build trusted relationships with business leaders across all countries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary escalation point for complex ER, disciplinary, and compliance matters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead workforce planning, organisational design, and headcount governance across all entities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the performance appraisal, salary review, and bonus cycles; make compensation, promotion, and bonus recommendations to the CEO.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regional HR Operations, Compliance &amp;amp; Governance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee end-to-end HR operations including talent acquisition and payroll across Singapore, Malaysia, the Philippines, Taiwan and Vietnam ensuring consistency, quality, and compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accountability for employment law compliance and statutory obligations across all jurisdictions&lt;/li&gt;
